    "client_msg_id": "370298d3-4962-41e6-80e2-7fbb5e79552e",
    "text": "There are many good ideas in there, but also some rather bad ones. In particular the choice of JavaScript as the language for doing calculations. JS isn't exactly known for its excellent number stack. I don't see it stated anywhere, but I suspect that calculang uses JS maths. rather than implementing something more robust and complete on top of JS (as XXX-to-JS compilers do).",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1708508948.383579",
    "parent_user_id": "UBN9AFS0N",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "9LGRc",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "There are many good ideas in there, but also some rather bad ones. In particular the choice of JavaScript as the language for doing calculations. JS isn't exactly known for its excellent number stack. I don't see it stated anywhere, but I suspect that calculang uses JS maths. rather than implementing something more robust and complete on top of JS (as XXX-to-JS compilers do)."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "linking-together",
    "channel_id": "C5U3SEW6A"
  },
